ACCF6E125A87456892E8191BEC029F75.description:
Indicate greater awareness of own
hunger and fullness.

99820EC09FDB459CA6F17F42E87C5559.description:
Indicate awareness of own hunger
and fullness.

9B1E9300EA934918A5D3BF8D19F6F2CE.description:
Indicate food preferences based on
familial and cultural practices and on
some knowledge of healthy choices.

D59519F3E5DD49C1B1980DE64F1380E9.description:
Demonstrate greater understanding
that eating a variety of food helps
the body grow and be healthy, and
choose from a greater variety of foods
at mealtimes.

E4F291BBA9244C408DBC12BECCAF9445.description:
Indicate food preferences that reflect
familial and cultural practices.

E0958F9FCDC445D3A0F21178AB86A74F.description:
Demonstrate a beginning understanding that eating a variety of food helps
the body grow and be healthy, and
choose from a variety of foods at
mealtimes.

46B8C4470C8E41C69CCFD3F5DD62744F.description:
Identify a larger variety of foods
and may know some of the related
food groups.

042338D6E44B472F83E1CAF333A3BEA7.description:
Show increased ability to follow transportation and pedestrian safety rules
with adult support and supervision.

2A3EBD4C78B34E5E837997B07665BD63.description:
Demonstrate increased ability to
follow emergency routines after
instruction and practice.

961A2D74852144BA88998894FC82EF31.description:
Follow safety rules more independently though may still need adult
support and prompting.

54BD9757DED642FFAE055515A5A09167.description:
Show beginning ability to follow transportation and pedestrian safety rules
with adult instruction and supervision.

CC2BE4DADC9E4EADB9050B23865E5311.description:
Begin to show ability to follow emergency routines after instruction and
practice (for example, a fire drill or
earthquake drill).

2477DF4D922E4B2DBDA05A257869C177.description:
Follow safety rules with adult
support and prompting.

18D0EB75184A44B99FE0D29E8260A034.description: Practice sun-safe actions with decreasing adult support and guidance.

7FCA504B9F7D44A2A8F34133AA89AC99.description:
Begin to practice sun-safe actions,
with adult support and guidance.

7681B5D32EDB499593BB5023959DD2EC.description:
Communicate to an adult about not
feeling well, feeling uncomfortable,
or about a special health need, with
more specificity and reliability.

4FD98F676CAA4C4B8474CA5D704321F0.description:
Demonstrate greater understanding
that health-care providers try to
keep people well and help them when
they are not well.

DD8297A5BD824674A7FE4B7A5E60A611.description:
Identify several different internal
body parts and demonstrate a
basic, limited knowledge of some
functions.

8A47A65E35594151812880BA3A5E3912.description:
Communicate to an adult about not
feeling well, feeling uncomfortable,
or about a special health need, with
varying specificity and reliability.

848D1B42F94A4C5A9445CCCA7C30AAEE.description:
Begin to understand that healthcare providers try to keep people well
and help them when they are not well.

0106A589DC69477F948A15E6786C2876.description:
Identify a few internal body parts
(most commonly the bones, brain,
and heart) but may not understand
their basic function.

5E2CCB9C1B634C46A1A6DCB07BE8F08F.description:
Demonstrate knowledge of more
steps of the routine for brushing and
when toothbrushing should be done,
with less adult supervision.

96C0065CC628486C9C9E674201DEE04A.description:
Demonstrate knowledge of some
steps of the routine for brushing
teeth, with adult supervision and
instruction.

2F896DA0C8B7416D8AF7065841900EC3.description:
Begin to independently practice health
habits that prevent infectious disease
and infestations (such as lice) when
appropriate, with less adult support,
instruction, and modeling.

9760C252BD2D4821A5052E0F3AAF6529.description:
Demonstrate knowledge of more
steps in the handwashing routine.

2FA20EBFEAAF4948AD906C306F148968.description:
Practice health habits that prevent
infectious diseases and infestations
(such as lice) when appropriate,
with adult support, instruction,
and modeling.

F7EC8A608ED540B5AACCCBBE476FFC3D.description:
Demonstrate knowledge of some
steps in the handwashing routine.

340B8255C534441AAB6263E9778D9D9E.description:
Engage in increasing amounts of
active play activities that enhance
leg and arm strength, muscular
endurance, and flexibility.

B0443755BB054C6FBDBC86C9ACD753C9.description:
Engage in active play activities that
enhance leg and arm strength,
muscular endurance, and flexibility.

C92F594DDD4841E48F9EBC0E74F7851E.description: Muscular Strength, Muscular Endurance, and Flexibility

DD39B642C6F34834826E19638CEFDFCE.description:
Engage in sustained active play of
increasing intensity that involves the
heart, the lungs, and the vascular
system.

86D7A973188B4052A30163FAC9BB79CD.description:
Engage in frequent bursts of active
play that involves the heart, the lungs,
and the vascular system.

8FA34A9F8B6647228814A9E0A87398F4.description:
Initiate more complex physical
activities for a sustained period
of time.

34BEA02AFB294412BFF5682888F24E78.description:
Initiate or engage in simple physical
activities for a short to moderate
period of time.

288227DCCEA940F3B0792BAFCE9CD125.description:
Demonstrate more precision and
efficiency during two-handed fine
motor activities.

59DFAD3C47024B49817401455BCAC4C5.description:
Can place an object or own body
in front of, to the side, or behind
something else with greater
accuracy.

1D6DA244267242ADA30A6E892A1FEFE7.description:
Can change directions quickly
and accurately.

1BADE241FA574E70BB74024056988FD4.description:
Begin to understand and distinguish
between the sides of the body.

8C70508C9C504BF385280D966EA00F26.description: Use any two body parts together.

097BD3E7BCD54374A360CE572FFD61DC.description:
Can place an object on top of
or under something with some
accuracy.

3BBA3CDD4DA74D30BCB347EC53282D58.description:
Move forward and backward or up
and down easily.

E1AA617446C346EA8BFF8FA6BF0F7E7A.description:
Distinguish movements that are up
and down and to the side of the body
(for example, understands “use that
side, now the other side”).

4971D5D541B944348011B79000E446D2.description:
Use own body, general space, and
other people’s space when locating or
relating to other people or objects in
space.

6E81DBADECCD4D33AE3AEBD1777D7088.description:
Use own body as reference point
when locating or relating to other
people or objects in space.

ED265CE200D346CF97DDFB2E26B37B76.description:
Demonstrate knowledge of an
increasing number of body parts.

BF8C701650904E69A07C96D47CC61AC9.description:
Demonstrate knowledge of the names
of body parts.

E6E5F2BB190547C9AF694FB2D905FD93.description:
Show increasing fine motor manipulative skills using hands and arms such
as in-hand manipulation, writing,
cutting, and dressing.

28EA18935670499BAAA3006D7561F41C.description:
Show gross motor manipulative skills
by using arms, hands, and feet with
increased coordination, such as rolling a ball underhand, tossing underhand, bouncing, catching, striking,
throwing overhand, and kicking.

E70269592D4147749CD8A9530472FC15.description:
Begin to show fine motor manipulative skills using hands and arms such
as in-hand manipulation, writing,
cutting, and dressing.

257AA456AC27495F9DA62E51CBFCC248.description:
Begin to show gross motor manipu -
lative skills by using arms, hands, and
feet, such as rolling a ball underhand,
tossing underhand, bouncing, catching, striking, throwing overhand, and
kicking.

493DA4FA21D64A44B397CC5679819914.description:
Demonstrate increasing ability and
body coordination in a variety of
locomotor skills, such as galloping,
sliding, hopping, and leaping.

C3165C6C0BF449339158EB6E61774154.description:
Jump for height (up or down) and for
distance with increasing competence.
Uses arm swing to aid forward jump.

6AF762A4D9FA44C8A584335F8FB24032.description:
Run with a longer stride length and
each foot off the ground for a greater
length of time. Opposition of arms
and legs is more consistent.

23C1F221B85B4CC98AE94A98EA304547.description:
Walk with balance, oppositional arm
movements, and relatively narrow
base of support (space between feet).

065AE7442CE84B5DB69465F6BA44F8B4.description:
Begin to demonstrate a variety of
locomotor skills, such as galloping,
sliding, hopping, and leaping.

402B6C3BDE7D44EEBA35A7977D3B8A1C.description:
Jump for height (up or down) and for
distance with beginning competence.

D67589F26D824CAC970673B54AC5084B.description:
Run with short stride length and
feet off the ground for a short period
of time. May show inconsistent
opposition of arms and legs.

4EDEE06F66174FFCBCA24A773CEB237D.description:
Walk with balance, not always stable,
oppositional arm movements still
developing, and relatively wide base
of support (space between feet).

C308233F85AE4B1E965724ACF11D3BCD.description:
Show increasing balance control while
moving in different directions and
when transitioning from one movement or position to another.

088C66F2902C4E28BA186B80D7B4AD67.description:
Show increasing balance and control
when holding still.

17E19A620A4840B4B8AAC1BE467021E4.description:
Maintain balance while in motion
when moving from one position to
another or when changing directions,
though balance may not be completely stable.

E56605DAE1054244BFB6C7B82972FB7E.description:
Maintain balance while holding still;
sometimes may need assistance.

B0FD29D3D74C40879E9D7E8FAE2AE5B8.description:
Communicate and express feelings
intentionally through dance.

113BC5F153964AB1B7699F1B0AA62CDB.description:
Improvise more complex dances
that have a beginning, middle, and an
end.

7C00003641FC4BB48F7164FB22C1D7B6.description:
Extend understanding and skills for
acting out and dramatizing through
music and movement patterns.

EA28A5C75CD848B8A67C76C324C24EEB.description:
Communicate feelings spontaneously
through dance and begin to express
simple feelings intentionally through
dance when prompted by adults.

FF148C23AFAB4EFFB4D73B3D384BA2E2.description:
Improvise simple dances that have
a beginning and an end.

317060F9116B479EB0AF98AE5381AC4F.description:
Begin to act out and dramatize
through music and movement
patterns.

A6DAD79D11534D4F84382CADCF8A0842.description: Create, Invent, and Express Through Dance

384A38271BAB4CAFA45047A572FCC286.description:
Demonstrate some advanced skills
in responding to tempo and timing
through movement.

AFEF802C1BB946B1A097F546434AAFC2.description:
Show advanced awareness and
coordination of movement with other
people in dance or when moving
in space.

A953AB2E82A147CE958C9EB43F6B3E06.description:
Continue to develop awareness
of body in space.

089A6A773D6F41CBB09550B762334718.description:
Begin to respond to tempo and
timing through movement.

C0075BD3D7894B5BBEF8640C0F301EC0.description:
Begin to be aware of other people
in dance or when moving in space.

077E7AD9ACE9409ABD79193F1782C5A9.description:
Begin to be aware of own body
in space.

BC0CCF34EBF3412480468F50615ED62A.description:
Use understanding of different steps
and movements to create or form
a dance.

88FDA9ED5DBC44D69877BCC93DC10C54.description:
Respond to instruction of more than
one skill at a time in movement, such
as turning, leaping, and turning again.
Often initiate a sequence of skills.

CF22EE0E4E1841D7859A975BA6914AFA.description:
Connect dance terminology with
demonstrated steps.

AA8591A6F5214E398DAEB7F3C2A4F989.description:
Further engage and participate
in dance movements.

55E3BA6347D04DBFB407EAB49F42E334.description:
Explore and use different steps
and movements to create or form
a dance.

44A49B403D7149AF83C77A526A06DE34.description:
Respond to instruction of one skill
at a time during movement, such as
a jump or fall.

BF28F0C2276942D29C9CB45207269E1B.description:
Begin to understand and use
vocabulary related to dance.

68D26418A3C54F1EBA4341F1B35B4B6C.description:
Create and use an increasing variety
of props, costumes and scenery to
enhance dramatization of familiar
stories and fantasy play with peers.

408F1575BA54406B8D72DB7E91AFF4F3.description:
Demonstrate extended role-play skills
with increased imagination and
creativity.

E74DF86A9A564F4C9AF9160D23D77DD7.description:
Add props and costumes to enhance
dramatization of familiar stories and
fantasy play with peers.

4DD1E205B4F1498FA030AF844FD288E3.description:
Demonstrate basic role-play skills
with imagination and creativity.

1FEA8A1187FC4917B79DF383C5025C1D.description: Develop Skills to Create, Invent, and Express Through Drama

2661F5E1A0C649ADBCCAD23A72A2B1B0.description:
Demonstrate knowledge of extended
plot and conflict of a participatory
drama.

C483641C622649339A6974C4A71B5F96.description:
Explain preferences and interests
related to participating in drama.

8DF514E6EEDA4AD490CE162099D7DA71.description:
Demonstrate a broader understanding
of drama vocabulary.

37D9DB28B66C410DB97CB0F1A157A1BE.description:
Demonstrate knowledge of simple
plot of a participatory drama.

2056F710BAC84709BD28E22E9A83532C.description:
Identify preferences and interests
related to participating in drama.

A1982087CF1E4CA4A16F9A3502C5D805.description:
Demonstrate an understanding of
simple drama vocabulary.

6E6D9DA45FC74F4081E8F58E235D99DE.description:
Explore, improvise, and create brief
melodies with voice or instrument.

8AA023AA7E9E4504A1F4E737FC2A6FAA.description:
Move or use body to demonstrate
beat, tempo, and style of music,
often intentionally.

36C2530115D845A196B5E1A35F2A42CF.description:
Continue to apply vocal and instrumental skills and use instruments
to produce more complex rhythms,
tones, melodies, and songs.

2C1EC85F25C44D898FB4694F682383E5.description:
Move or use body to demonstrate
beat and tempo, often spontaneously.

CE93A96FF04943D0B1EFA3217FAD11E6.description:
Explore vocal and instrumental skills
and use instruments to produce
simple rhythms and tones.

D532D213592E4BCBA1D1E75AAD1BDC5E.description: Create, Invent, and Express Through Music

D07D6F887F3441338863AC3975C871E2.description:
Extend vocal exploration; sing
repetitive patterns and entire songs
alone and with others in wider
ranges of pitch.

AD3767A06CAB434BBE0C0788A5F77BC5.description:
Become more able to discriminate
between different voices and various instrumental and environmental
sounds. Follow words in a song.

C3D23C2279C84AA79BFEC4F8A1C82255.description:
Explore vocally; sing repetitive
patterns and parts of songs alone
and with others.

21093C648A26407D8AF92FD239F9607A.description:
Begin to discriminate between different voices and certain instrumental
and environmental sounds. Follow
words in a song.

576E47999D2A4E9F949498EA7BA60FBC.description:
Use body movement freely and
more accurately to respond to beat,
dynamics, and tempo of music.

D06C3BE337464A1C85434D7E0E1DE45E.description:
Identify the sources of a wider
variety of music and music-like
sounds.

CE14C55104FF4556B9A2A57C8023E4E7.description:
Demonstrate more complex repeating
melody and rhythm patterns.

192D95645E4843D7857F2E6DE5A4BBA5.description:
Verbally reflect on music and
describe music by using an
expanded vocabulary.

73F3960226A04DF199D9AED5443BE6CC.description:
Use body movement freely to respond
loosely to beat—loud versus quiet
(dynamics)—and tempo.

DF42FFF3D32A4D96B179AA12AE98484E.description:
Identify the sources of a limited
variety of musical sounds.

64C7FAC593BA40EF8851112C8270E964.description:
Recognize simple repeating melody
and rhythm patterns.

7546942F5C844BF98487C954F4AE5BBB.description:
Sustain attention and begin to reflect
verbally about music; demonstrate
familiarity with words that describe
music.

FE5A4F23565249A89D6509AD0DE4B1B2.description:
Use intensity of marks and color
more frequently to express a feeling
or mood.

91A83D0C59CA4CC7BEE5D17400964BB5.description:
Draw more detailed figures or
objects with more control of line
and shape.

E65FC52C91DF4B7D85730AB8229E9D4D.description:
Intentionally create content in a
work of art.

7981A218764A44C2AE57267C0A7E02A3.description:
Begin to use intensity of marks and
color to express a feeling or mood.

AC9781E2BCA74544B9182E03CB9101BC.description: Begin to draw figures or objects.

DA2AC668B4964F1985CCF5575E70D0CE.description:
Create art and sometimes name
the work.

BB02E17015D74B38A813A0290DFBC02E.description: Create, Invent, and Express Through Visual Art

663432E6B0624A979D4815BC8459C463.description:
Demonstrate increasing coordination
and motor control when working
with visual arts tools.

29C2D81A643A4A4889EC2A18D1AF6E1A.description:
Recognize and name materials
and tools used for visual arts.

3EC5772CF2CD4AC6A630EA9B63A2B451.description:
Use paper and other materials to
make two- and three-dimensional
assembled works.

5B2859E00AAB48138C8C3D2F690447D6.description:
Make more representational forms
out of dough or clay, using tools
(for example, a rolling pin or a garlic
press).

B9DB1D64EB724A33931675BCAE93F02F.description:
Begin to create representative paintings or drawings that approximate or
depict people, animals, and objects.

5D8F09FCBC2645B49BD2B5F292B2EB07.description:
Draw single circle and add lines
to create representations of people
and things.

092EE5DB55524A21883F4F52D530A4E1.description:
Demonstrate some motor control
when working with visual arts tools.

50B9138E53344BA88D06CF09389A330E.description:
Begin to recognize and name
materials and tools used for visual
arts.

373DF5C1851E4FA598CDE0A2447F74B8.description: Begin to use paper and other materials to assemble simple collages.

00EEC042A2B34AEC9952015E7599AD0A.description:
Make somewhat regular-shaped balls
and coils out of dough or clay.

AA0DD083A02040C1BCC48D9D2B8FEAA5.description:
Begin to create paintings or drawings
that suggest people, animals, and
objects.

86C73B7278F848308B3DDC64EE316F1D.description:
Make straight and curved marks
and lines; begin to draw rough circle
shapes.

78E583531A5B447AB491EC148DB67219.description:
Choose own art for display in the
classroom or for inclusion in a portfolio or book and explain her or his
ideas in some detail.

CB7D25A1205947BF942BB94E06DB5D1B.description:
Enjoy and engage with displays of
visual art. May expand critical assessment of visual art to include preferences for types of artwork or art
activities.

6CF53760C009499DAA1CC2D1971E1D19.description:
Begin to plan art and show increasing
care and persistence in completing it.

390531DEB0CE4454B9DA69AFF07490C6.description:
Communicate about elements
appearing in art (such as line, texture,
or perspective), and describe how
objects are positioned in the artwork.

34A6832AEA114FC99F21C5A6746B95D3.description:
Choose own art for display in the
classroom or for inclusion in a
portfolio or book and briefly
explain choice.

4CDC8B2710B146DC9B8955DB959FF1FE.description:
Enjoy and engage with displays of
visual art, inside or outside the classroom. Begin to express preferences
for some art activities or materials.

67EC465105174801BF43E2F8B7DB2BFE.description:
Create marks with crayons, paints,
and chalk and then identify them;
mold and build with dough and clay
and then identify them.

85DA8CCA70714A96AD18BE011DD1C895.description:
Notice and communicate about
objects or forms that appear in art.
